PBSPro

```json
{
  "application": "PBSPro",
  "description": "This script is a converter for NQS scripts to PBSPro scripts. It handles various NQS options and converts them to their PBSPro equivalents, including resource requests, job attributes, and execution settings. It parses NQS date/time specifications and converts them to PBSPro format, while also adjusting time zone settings. The script also processes resource limits and SRFS requests for appropriate PBSPro translation.",
  "dependencies": [
    "awk",
    "date"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": [
    "standard input",
    "standard output",
    "standard error",
    "temporary file storage"
  ],
  "usage": "This script takes two arguments: the NQS script file to be converted and the optional output PBSPro script file. If the second argument is not provided, the output file will be named as the input file with the extension '.new'. For example, 'nqs_script.sh' will be converted to 'nqs_script.sh.new'."
}
```
